<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-04-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-04-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="449" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d449">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 1229/9–10.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Vice-Consul <persName type="from">Sarle</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Third Assistant Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Zanzibar</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-04-21"><hi rend="italic">April 21,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 39.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that the
                            jurisdiction hitherto exercised by the German consular court in Zanzibar
                            has been transferred to the British consular court as from March 30.
                            Inclosed is a copy of official notice.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">A. L. Sarle.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>